def: A constellation. See Auriga, and Wagones.
The quality or state of being venerable; venerableness. Dr. H.More.
To retire; to go back. [Obs.] W. Hales.
Relating to accretion; increasing, or adding to, by growth.Glanvill.
In a nimble manner; with agility; with light, quick motion.
One who, or that which, lights; as, a lighter of lamps.
Worthy of being approved; meritorious.-- Ap*prov"a*ble*ness, n.
The process of becoming white, or developing white patches, orstreaks.
